criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Male or female subjects, 25-45 yrs;

          2. Non-specific and/or moderate constipation;

          3. Irregular or occasional gastrointestinal disorders (flatulence, gurgling, feeling
             heavy after eating, abdominal pain);

          4. Slow transit or irregular bowels movements (abnormal feces solidity, bowel movements
             decreased, e.g. every 2-3 days or less than 3 times per week).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Diagnosed as chronic constipation;

          2. Treated gastrointestinal symptoms;

          3. Lactose Intolerance;

          4. Treatment by analgesic such as aspirin and paracetamol;

          5. Had laxatives or other remedies to promote digestion 2 weeks prior to the study start;

          6. Consuming dairy products or supplements containing pro/pre-biotic 10 days prior to the
             study start;

          7. Currently suffering from diarrhea.
